The project will be assigned in Week 6. Students will work in teams of two to formulate, analyze, and solve a mathematical imaging reconstruction problem.
Each team will:

define the forward model;
implement reconstruction methods in Python;
analyze parameter sensitivity;
interpret reconstruction quality;
submit a written report and code;
complete an individual oral defense.

Matrix or Vector?
For visualization, a grayscale image is naturally a matrix:

U \in \mathbb{R}^{m \times n}

For linear algebra, we often reshape it as a vector:

x = \operatorname{vec}(U) \in \mathbb{R}^{mn}

This lets imaging problems use the tools of linear systems.
